name "guestvlan"
vlan 999
name "disabled"
!
int vlan 5 
 ip address 192.168.5.3 255.255.255.0
 standby 1 ip 192.168.5.1
 standby 1 priority 254
 standby 1 preempt
 ip helper-address 198.18.133.1                  
 ip ospf 1 area 0
 no shutdown
!
pnp startup-vlan 5
!

 ip address 192.168.10.3 255.255.255.0

int vlan 20

 standby 1 priority 254

 ip helper-address 198.18.133.1                  
 ip ospf 1 area 0
 no shutdown
int vlan 30

 standby 1 priority 254
 standby 1 preempt
 ip helper-address 198.18.133.1                  
 ip ospf 1 area 0
 no shutdown
int vlan 40
 ip address 192.168.40.3 255.255.255.0
 standby 1 ip 192.168.40.1
 standby 1 priority 254
 standby 1 preempt
 ip helper-address 198.18.133.1                  
 ip ospf 1 area 0
 no shutdown
int vlan 999
 ip address 192.168.99.3 255.255.255.0

 standby 1 priority 254
 standby 1 preempt
 ip helper-address 198.18.133.1

 no shutdown
!

router ospf 1

autoconf enable<IQ>yes<R>y
#END_INTERACTIVE

template ACCESS_POINT

 switchport trunk native vlan 10

!
template WORKSTATION

 switchport mode access

!

 switchport mode access
!
template BASECONFIG
 description BASE CONFIG

 switchport mode access

 spanning-tree bpduguard enable

#end
!

{"name":"{{TemplateName}}","description":"API Example Template Deployment","tags":[],"deviceTypes":[{"productFamily":"Switches and Hubs","productSeries":"Cisco Catalyst 9300 Series Switches"}],"softwareType":"IOS","softwareVariant":"XE","softwareVersion":null,"templateContent":"##Automated Uplink Description Script
##This will always ensure the uplink descriptions are correct to upstream
##Switches within the infrastructure
event manager applet update-port
 event neighbor-discovery interface regexp GigabitEthernet.* cdp add
 action 101 regexp "(Switch|Router)" "$_nd_cdp_capabilities_string"
 action 102 if $_regexp_result eq "1"
 action 103  cli command "enable"
 action 104  cli command "config t"
 action 105  cli command "interface $_nd_local_intf_name"
 action 106  regexp "^([^\.]+)\." "$_nd_cdp_entry_name" match host
 action 107  regexp "^([^\.]+)" "$_nd_port_id" match connectedport
 action 108  cli command "no description"
 action 109  cli command "description Uplink to $host - $connectedport"
 action 110  cli command "interface port-channel 1"
 action 111  cli command "no description"
 action 112  cli command "description Uplink to $host"
 action 113  cli command "end"
 action 114  cli command "write"
 action 115 end
!
